# Reflection

One of the main challenges in this assignment was selecting the most appropriate GitHub project template.
While multiple templates were available, it required careful analysis to determine which one best supports Agile workflows and the needs of the Assignment Tracker System.

Customizing the Kanban board also presented challenges, particularly in deciding which additional columns to include.
Adding columns such as "Testing" and "Blocked" required understanding how tasks flow through development and identifying potential bottlenecks.

Another challenge was linking issues from Assignment 6 to the Kanban board and ensuring that all tasks were properly tracked. 
This required attention to detail to maintain consistency and traceability.

When comparing GitHub Projects to other tools such as Trello and Jira, GitHub offers strong integration with code and issues, making it convenient for developers.
However, tools like Jira provide more advanced Agile features, while Trello offers a simpler and more user-friendly interface.

Overall, this assignment improved understanding of Kanban boards, 
workflow visualization, and Agile project management tools.
